    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering a mechanically sorted 2004 BMW M3 (E46) powered by the S54B32 3.2L inline-six with individual throttle bodies. This chassis has undergone critical preventive maintenance, including a comprehensive double-VANOS overhaul and a structural reinforcement of the rear subframe. Power is sent through a 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox to a factory limited-slip differential, ensuring linear torque delivery. The suspension geometry is maintained by refreshed control arm bushings and Bilstein dampers, providing excellent damping rebound and lateral composure. While the exterior displays minor patina commensurate with a well-loved driver's car in good condition, the valvetrain is quiet, and the engine pulls strongly to its 8,000 RPM redline with consistent compression across all cylinders.",
      "price": 31500.0,
